WEBVTT

00:07.050 --> 00:09.139
- ♪ Down in the valley

00:11.141 --> 00:13.491
♪ Valley so low

00:13.535 --> 00:16.494
- Looks like somebody
was living here.

00:16.538 --> 00:18.757
Adam Lowry and Bess McTeer
were headed there

00:18.801 --> 00:20.194
with Julian...

00:20.237 --> 00:21.499
and someone was waiting
for them.

00:21.543 --> 00:23.762
The guy back at the dorms
with the ponytail--

00:23.806 --> 00:25.460
I saw him at the motel
when we went to speak

00:25.503 --> 00:28.158
to the manager.
- Marin is Julian's mother.

00:28.202 --> 00:30.508
Where is she?
- We have reason to believe

00:30.552 --> 00:32.293
her body was dumped in a lake

00:32.336 --> 00:34.556
near Mosswood.
- There are abuses

00:34.599 --> 00:37.080
all over Mosswood
and you were in charge.

00:37.124 --> 00:40.040
- I allowed horrible things
to happen, I did.

00:40.083 --> 00:42.085
When I saw Julian's face...

00:42.129 --> 00:44.131
I woke up...

00:44.174 --> 00:45.306
and I knew what I had to do.

00:45.349 --> 00:47.308
And I changed Mosswood
for good.

00:47.351 --> 00:49.788
- That hooded thing
that you keep seeing--

00:49.832 --> 00:52.052
I'd stare it down
next time you see it.

00:52.095 --> 00:53.575
'Cause it'll ruin you
if you let it.

00:57.579 --> 01:00.147
- Oh, shit.

01:00.190 --> 01:02.410
♪

01:07.415 --> 01:14.465
♪

01:37.445 --> 01:44.495
♪

01:51.894 --> 01:59.119
♪

02:31.194 --> 02:32.891
- All right, everyone,
remain calm.

02:32.935 --> 02:34.632
I need you to come inside
right now.

02:34.676 --> 02:36.286
Yep, put the baskets down.

02:36.330 --> 02:38.462
Leave what you have
in your hands on the ground.

02:38.506 --> 02:40.899
Put down the baskets.
- Everybody sit down.

02:40.943 --> 02:42.466
Legs out in front.

02:42.510 --> 02:44.468
Cross your feet for me.
That's it.

02:44.512 --> 02:45.904
Cross your feet.
- Hey, this is

02:45.948 --> 02:47.471
private property.
- Ma'am, please sit down.

02:47.515 --> 02:49.473
We have a warrant
to search these premises.

02:49.517 --> 02:50.474
- A warrant

02:50.518 --> 02:52.346
for Julian Walker.

02:52.389 --> 02:53.695
What are you talking about?

02:53.738 --> 02:55.610
He's in the custody
of Social Services.

02:55.653 --> 02:57.655
- Julian went missing
from the group home

02:57.699 --> 02:59.657
earlier this morning.

03:01.529 --> 03:02.704
How?

03:02.747 --> 03:04.488
- That's what we're trying
to find out.

03:04.532 --> 03:07.230
- Ma'am, please sit down.

03:07.274 --> 03:08.362
- He's not here!
- Right now.

03:08.405 --> 03:10.320
- You need to tell me
what happened.

03:10.364 --> 03:11.713
- Ms. Walker, just calm down.
- Don't tell me to calm down!

03:11.756 --> 03:13.671
You took my son away from me,
and now you don't know

03:13.715 --> 03:15.499
where he is, and you're
telling me to calm down?

03:15.543 --> 03:17.458
This is bullshit.
- Ma'am, you can't leave.

03:17.501 --> 03:18.676
- Ms. Walker!
- You can't leave.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.678
- No, I can leave!
I have to find my son!

03:20.722 --> 03:23.333
You get your hands off of me!
I didn't do anything wrong!

03:23.377 --> 03:24.465
You can't do this to me!

03:25.727 --> 03:27.250
- Ms. Walker, be reasonable.
- No.

03:27.294 --> 03:28.730
You're wasting time.

03:28.773 --> 03:30.297
Don't touch me!

03:32.473 --> 03:34.431
♪

03:34.475 --> 03:35.606
You don't know
what you're doing.

03:35.650 --> 03:37.304
- Come on.

03:37.347 --> 03:39.523
♪

03:41.525 --> 03:43.397
♪

03:43.440 --> 03:46.617
- And you saw him
go into the bedroom?

03:46.661 --> 03:48.358
- Yes.

03:48.402 --> 03:49.359
- And you heard
nothing unusual?

03:49.403 --> 03:50.665
- No.

03:57.019 --> 03:59.239
- Detective.

04:00.544 --> 04:02.242
Can I help you?
- Yeah.

04:02.285 --> 04:04.548
Can you do me a favor?
I want to check upstairs.

04:06.028 --> 04:08.378
- Sure.

04:13.601 --> 04:20.651
♪

04:25.090 --> 04:28.006
- When did you realize
Julian was missing?

04:28.050 --> 04:29.312
♪

04:29.356 --> 04:31.749
- 4:40, maybe 4:45 a.m.

04:31.793 --> 04:33.751
- None of the other kids
saw anything?

04:33.795 --> 04:35.753
Nobody saw him leave?

04:35.797 --> 04:37.799
- Everybody was asleep.

04:37.842 --> 04:44.893
♪

04:50.464 --> 04:52.335
Oh, he wrote that number there.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.598
I--I don't know
whose it is.

04:54.642 --> 04:56.774
♪

04:56.818 --> 04:58.689
- It's mine.

04:58.733 --> 04:59.777
♪

04:59.821 --> 05:01.605
How was his mood last night?

05:01.649 --> 05:04.347
- Honestly, he seemed...

05:04.391 --> 05:06.349
dissociated.

05:06.393 --> 05:13.443
♪

05:15.793 --> 05:17.534
- Do you keep sunflower seeds

05:17.578 --> 05:19.797
in the house?

05:19.841 --> 05:22.365
- Not usually, no.

05:22.409 --> 05:25.629
♪

05:25.673 --> 05:28.066
Hey--hey!

05:28.110 --> 05:35.335
♪

05:47.869 --> 05:54.876
♪

06:11.849 --> 06:13.851
- Next time my brother
has a party, I'm bringing you.

06:13.895 --> 06:15.505
- Fine.
- I don't want to see you like

06:15.549 --> 06:17.507
throwing up all over the floor.
- Yeah.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.467
- This guy, right here.

06:20.510 --> 06:22.556
- You, like--you get sick
from, like, too much candy.

06:22.599 --> 06:23.687
Such a lightweight.

06:29.432 --> 06:32.130
- It's just nicotine.
- I don't care about that.

06:32.174 --> 06:33.610
You guys see anything parked

06:33.654 --> 06:35.873
in that spot lately?
- Yeah.

06:35.917 --> 06:37.701
Fucking camper van.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.703
Took a piss on the back tire
and it honked.

06:39.747 --> 06:42.445
Scared the shit out of me.

06:42.489 --> 06:44.882
- You happen to see who it was
that was inside?

06:44.926 --> 06:46.710
- Window had curtains.

06:46.754 --> 06:48.146
- Anybody remember
anything else?

06:48.190 --> 06:49.583
License plate,
anything like that?

06:49.626 --> 06:50.932
- It was a shitty brown.

06:52.760 --> 06:54.892
- Yeah.

06:54.936 --> 06:59.941
♪

07:01.812 --> 07:03.901
- Just hang on.

07:03.945 --> 07:06.643
We gotta call and get
an Amber Alert.

07:06.687 --> 07:08.906
Julian didn't run away,
he was abducted.

07:08.950 --> 07:11.822
There was a van that was across
from the foster house.

07:11.866 --> 07:13.694
That means it might not be
Vera Walker after all.

07:13.737 --> 07:15.435
- Wait, slow down.
What do you mean, a van?

07:15.478 --> 07:17.785
- There was a brown camper van.

07:17.828 --> 07:19.569
It was seen
in the parking lot last night.

07:19.613 --> 07:21.223
- Detective Ambrose.

07:21.266 --> 07:22.833
♪

07:22.877 --> 07:24.226
I thought I made it clear

07:24.269 --> 07:25.575
you weren't needed here
anymore.

07:25.619 --> 07:26.924
- Yeah, we got a missing child.

07:26.968 --> 07:28.926
I'm not going home
until we find him.

07:28.970 --> 07:31.625
Look, there was a van
that was parked across

07:31.668 --> 07:32.626
from the foster home.

07:32.669 --> 07:34.497
Someone was stalking Julian.

07:34.541 --> 07:36.499
They were there last night,
waiting.

07:36.543 --> 07:38.632
- Hold on, hold on.
Who are "they"?

07:38.675 --> 07:40.634
- I don't know.

07:40.677 --> 07:42.592
But we need an alert.

07:42.636 --> 07:45.203
Look, I could be wrong,
but I think I'm right.

07:45.247 --> 07:46.770
♪

07:46.814 --> 07:47.945
Chief.

07:47.989 --> 07:49.947
Julian Walker is slipping away
from us.

07:49.991 --> 07:51.558
We don't have time...
- This is Heather Novack,

07:51.601 --> 07:53.473
Keller PD.
We need an Amber Alert

07:53.516 --> 07:55.953
for Julian Walker, age 13.

07:55.997 --> 07:57.520
Possible abduction.

07:57.564 --> 08:00.784
We're looking
for a brown camper van.

08:00.828 --> 08:01.959
♪

08:08.400 --> 08:12.187
♪

08:14.624 --> 08:18.585
♪

08:18.628 --> 08:20.369
- I did.

08:20.412 --> 08:21.588
♪

08:21.631 --> 08:23.285
What about you?

08:23.328 --> 08:26.114
Do you have those?

08:26.157 --> 08:27.898
- Yeah.

08:27.942 --> 08:31.380
♪

08:31.423 --> 08:34.296
- Still nothing on N.C.I.C.

08:36.428 --> 08:38.169
- He was telling me all along

08:38.213 --> 08:40.911
there was a hooded thing
coming after him.

08:41.695 --> 08:44.001
It was all real.

08:49.267 --> 08:51.400
I need to talk to her.

09:01.105 --> 09:04.239
I'm sorry
this is happening to you.

09:04.282 --> 09:06.154
- If you really are,
then get them

09:06.197 --> 09:08.112
to let me out of here.

09:09.374 --> 09:10.985
- You'd have
to cooperate first.

09:12.377 --> 09:15.076
They lost my son,
and then they raided my home

09:15.119 --> 09:16.425
and accused me of taking him.

09:16.468 --> 09:19.210
I've got nothing to say.

09:19.254 --> 09:23.258
- I had nothing to do
with that raid.

09:23.301 --> 09:24.694
- And yet here you are,

09:24.738 --> 09:27.088
on the other side
of this table.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.139
- There was a van--
a brown camper van--

09:35.183 --> 09:37.968
that was parked across
from the foster home.

09:47.195 --> 09:50.198
You know who's driving
that van, don't you?

09:52.374 --> 09:54.550
Vera...

09:56.117 --> 09:58.380
We're gonna lose him.

10:00.556 --> 10:03.124
We have to work together.

10:09.086 --> 10:11.001
- I want to speak to my lawyer.

10:15.353 --> 10:17.442
- You...

10:21.272 --> 10:24.536
You hurt him when you do that.

10:24.580 --> 10:27.583
You know, what you're doing
right now, you're hurting him.

10:29.150 --> 10:30.499
- Harry, saving my son

10:30.542 --> 10:32.544
isn't gonna save you.

10:38.376 --> 10:43.338
♪

10:45.035 --> 10:46.558
- Harry.

10:46.602 --> 10:48.517
We got something.

10:48.560 --> 10:52.521
♪

10:54.392 --> 10:56.525
♪

10:56.568 --> 10:59.049
What is it?

10:59.093 --> 11:05.577
♪

11:08.624 --> 11:15.675
♪

11:20.592 --> 11:22.246
- No.

11:22.290 --> 11:23.770
It was just like this.

11:23.813 --> 11:25.380
- Canadian plates.

11:25.423 --> 11:27.556
Have you run those yet?
- Yeah.

11:27.599 --> 11:30.211
The plates were reported stolen
off another vehicle

11:30.254 --> 11:32.387
in Quebec three weeks ago.

11:32.430 --> 11:39.481
♪

11:41.178 --> 11:44.051
- Looks like they ditched this
in a hurry.

11:44.094 --> 11:51.145
♪

11:51.841 --> 11:54.235
We'd better get the dogs
out here.

11:54.278 --> 11:56.280
♪

11:59.327 --> 12:06.377
♪

12:15.865 --> 12:23.133
♪

12:24.221 --> 12:25.440
Hey.

12:25.483 --> 12:27.094
Heather.

12:27.137 --> 12:31.141
♪

12:37.931 --> 12:40.281
It has knots.

12:40.324 --> 12:42.457
Like a cincture.

12:44.285 --> 12:45.503
- Yeah.

12:45.547 --> 12:48.550
It's a type of belt
that's worn by monks.

12:48.593 --> 12:50.682
As a kid, I learned
that the Franciscans

12:50.726 --> 12:53.207
tied three knots in theirs.

12:53.903 --> 12:56.471
- Let's find out
who wears five.

12:58.255 --> 13:00.301
- Yeah.

13:00.344 --> 13:02.564
- They're charging you
with resisting arrest.

13:02.607 --> 13:04.609
I expect they're gonna
hold you overnight

13:04.653 --> 13:06.350
before they release you.
- None of that matters

13:06.394 --> 13:08.222
right now.

13:08.265 --> 13:10.877
I need you to go find Terry
and give him a message.

13:10.920 --> 13:12.400
♪

13:12.443 --> 13:15.316
Tell him to go see
The Grey Daughters.

13:15.359 --> 13:17.187
♪

13:22.932 --> 13:27.502
♪

13:27.545 --> 13:29.939
- Well, the five knots stand

13:29.983 --> 13:31.549
for poverty, chastity,

13:31.593 --> 13:34.552
obedience, enclosure,
and detachment.

13:34.596 --> 13:35.945
- Ah.

13:35.989 --> 13:37.947
And every nun wears
one of these--

13:37.991 --> 13:40.471
just like this?
- Every nun of our order.

13:42.734 --> 13:44.911
- Well, we have convents
all over the Northeast

13:44.954 --> 13:46.390
and Canada.

13:46.434 --> 13:50.264
I'd say over 500 sisters
active today.

13:50.307 --> 13:52.527
- I need a list of their names

13:52.570 --> 13:54.529
- Sure.

13:54.572 --> 13:57.314
- And who else
would have access

13:57.358 --> 13:59.708
to the habits
that the sisters wear?

13:59.751 --> 14:02.406
- Well, uh, we have laypeople
coming through...

14:02.450 --> 14:04.713
- It's her.
- And volunteers,

14:04.756 --> 14:07.368
maintenance people...
- It's her.

14:07.411 --> 14:09.544
- Excuse me.

14:09.587 --> 14:11.415
What?

14:11.459 --> 14:12.634
♪

14:12.677 --> 14:14.723
- Marin.

14:14.766 --> 14:17.421
I don't understand...

14:17.465 --> 14:18.727
♪

14:18.770 --> 14:21.469
- Sister, uh,
there's a woman here--

14:21.512 --> 14:23.732
do you know...

14:23.775 --> 14:26.474
the woman right there?
- Oh, of course.

14:26.517 --> 14:27.954
That's Laura.

14:27.997 --> 14:29.259
♪

14:29.303 --> 14:30.608
- Laura.

14:30.652 --> 14:33.437
- She's--she was living here
for some time.

14:33.481 --> 14:35.439
She left just a few weeks ago.

14:35.483 --> 14:36.440
- Hmm.

14:36.484 --> 14:39.748
♪

14:39.791 --> 14:41.576
- Laura came in
three years ago.

14:41.619 --> 14:43.970
We help run a recovery center

14:44.013 --> 14:46.407
and she admitted herself.

14:46.450 --> 14:48.452
She got sober and ended up

14:48.496 --> 14:50.977
staying on with us.

14:51.020 --> 14:53.022
- Almost.

14:53.066 --> 14:54.763
She was quite dedicated.

14:54.806 --> 14:57.722
Well, she--
she also struggled.

14:57.766 --> 15:00.247
Nothing came easy for her.

15:00.290 --> 15:02.597
I had hoped that
she would take her vows,

15:02.640 --> 15:05.426
but that's not what she wanted.

15:06.383 --> 15:08.559
This was her room.

15:10.822 --> 15:12.476
It's so strange--

15:12.520 --> 15:14.043
her father's looking
for her, too.

15:14.087 --> 15:16.350
He came here just last night.

15:18.395 --> 15:21.355
- He picked up a box
of Laura's belongings.

15:21.398 --> 15:23.618
I didn't get his name.

15:23.661 --> 15:25.402
- Um...

15:25.446 --> 15:27.404
long hair--grey--

15:27.448 --> 15:29.667
tied back in a ponytail.

15:32.061 --> 15:34.759
- How long ago did you say
she left?

15:34.803 --> 15:36.848
- I would say--
must have been four

15:36.892 --> 15:39.329
or five weeks ago.

15:42.376 --> 15:47.642
♪

15:47.685 --> 15:50.036
Is she okay?
Did something happen?

15:50.079 --> 15:52.386
- It's important
that we find her.

15:52.429 --> 15:53.691
♪

15:53.735 --> 15:56.085
Did she say where
she was going?

15:56.129 --> 15:57.782
♪

15:57.826 --> 15:59.828
- She wouldn't say.

15:59.871 --> 16:02.309
♪

16:02.352 --> 16:04.050
- Marin, my God.

16:04.093 --> 16:05.834
Welcome home.

16:07.836 --> 16:14.886
♪

16:17.585 --> 16:19.674
We've made a lot of changes
since you left.

16:19.717 --> 16:22.068
For the better.

16:22.111 --> 16:24.635
You have no idea
how much we missed you.

16:25.549 --> 16:27.682
- I missed you too.

16:27.725 --> 16:29.423
- We have a bed for you.
I can have D'Nell

16:29.466 --> 16:31.642
get it ready for you.
- I'm not staying.

16:32.904 --> 16:36.865
I'm here for Julian.

16:40.738 --> 16:42.479
- I wanna thank you
for everything

16:42.523 --> 16:44.525
you've done for him,
and everything you tried

16:44.568 --> 16:46.396
to do for me, but I'm ready

16:46.440 --> 16:48.572
to be his mom again.

16:52.881 --> 16:55.449
- I want him back.

16:55.492 --> 16:57.668
I need to be with him.

16:59.844 --> 17:02.543
- I know you haven't had
an easy time since you left us.

17:02.586 --> 17:05.415
I heard about rehab
in Providence.

17:05.459 --> 17:06.938
And in Manchester.

17:08.766 --> 17:11.595
- I've been clean three years.

17:11.639 --> 17:13.510
I've worked the steps.
I'm a different person now.

17:13.554 --> 17:15.556
- Marin...

17:15.599 --> 17:18.124
you're a stranger to Julian.

17:18.167 --> 17:20.474
To disturb things now
at his age, that--

17:20.517 --> 17:22.780
that would be harmful.

17:24.695 --> 17:26.480
- So you never told him
about me?

17:26.523 --> 17:28.786
- I didn't see the point.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.745
You left us.
We had no idea

17:30.788 --> 17:33.139
if you were ever coming back.

17:33.182 --> 17:35.576
- You knew what
I was going through

17:35.619 --> 17:37.708
and you took advantage of that.
- I did everything I could do

17:37.752 --> 17:38.970
to help you.
- You took over

17:39.014 --> 17:40.755
being his mother
and you didn't give any room

17:40.798 --> 17:42.583
for me.
- Marin, you barely wanted

17:42.626 --> 17:44.454
to hold him.

17:46.543 --> 17:48.850
- I want to see him.

17:51.548 --> 17:53.507
- No, I don't think
that's a good idea.

17:53.550 --> 17:54.986
- You can't just decide that.

17:55.030 --> 17:56.597
- I can.

17:56.640 --> 17:58.642
I have a legal right.

17:58.686 --> 18:02.559
You abandoned him,
and I'm his mother now.

18:02.603 --> 18:04.953
And now I think
you should leave, please.

18:10.785 --> 18:12.613
- Please go.

18:15.833 --> 18:22.884
♪

18:30.021 --> 18:37.072
♪

18:45.733 --> 18:52.783
♪

18:57.788 --> 19:01.836
♪

19:03.751 --> 19:10.801
♪

19:30.647 --> 19:33.084
- Hey, get out of here!

19:33.128 --> 19:34.912
You can't be here.

19:35.957 --> 19:37.698
- Get off me!

19:37.741 --> 19:38.960
He's mine!

19:39.003 --> 19:40.657
He's my kid!

19:40.701 --> 19:43.007
He's my kid!

19:45.358 --> 19:47.011
- Leave her alone.

19:48.970 --> 19:50.276
- Hey...

19:50.319 --> 19:51.973
- I have no idea. I don't know.

19:52.016 --> 19:54.062
- She needs to get off
the grounds.

19:54.105 --> 19:55.324
- It's okay.

19:55.368 --> 19:57.021
I've got her.

19:57.065 --> 20:00.895
It's okay. Come on.

20:02.810 --> 20:06.030
♪

20:06.074 --> 20:08.555
It was only a dream.

20:08.598 --> 20:13.299
♪

20:13.342 --> 20:15.649
It was only a dream.

20:18.695 --> 20:24.658
♪

20:24.701 --> 20:26.790
- Please, Bess.
You know this isn't right.

20:26.834 --> 20:28.662
♪

20:28.705 --> 20:30.054
You were--

20:30.098 --> 20:32.013
You were there.

20:32.056 --> 20:34.145
You know.

20:34.189 --> 20:39.934
♪

20:39.977 --> 20:41.327
- I know.

20:41.370 --> 20:42.328
♪

20:42.371 --> 20:44.678
- Please.

20:44.721 --> 20:46.680
I really need your help.

20:46.723 --> 20:50.161
♪

20:55.166 --> 20:56.864
Hello?

20:56.907 --> 20:58.779
- Hey.
Uh, we're on the road.

20:58.822 --> 21:00.824
Everything's going fine.

21:00.868 --> 21:02.957
You didn't have any problems

21:03.000 --> 21:04.350
getting away?
No one followed you?

21:04.393 --> 21:05.829
[peppy music playing
over radio]

21:05.873 --> 21:07.918
- Uh, no, no.

21:07.962 --> 21:10.660
We're all good.

21:10.704 --> 21:12.662
- He's enjoying the drive

21:12.706 --> 21:14.142
in the big, wide world.

21:14.185 --> 21:15.752
♪

21:15.796 --> 21:17.363
We all are.

21:17.406 --> 21:18.973
- Bess...

21:19.016 --> 21:20.148
♪

21:20.191 --> 21:21.802
Thank you.

21:21.845 --> 21:22.977
♪

21:23.020 --> 21:24.892
- We'll--we'll check in...

21:24.935 --> 21:26.023
later, okay?

21:26.067 --> 21:27.634
When we get closer.

21:27.677 --> 21:29.157
- Okay.

21:29.200 --> 21:31.028
♪

21:31.072 --> 21:35.119
- Vera sends you a kiss.

21:35.163 --> 21:37.687
- When we get to Niagara Falls,
how close up can we get?

21:37.731 --> 21:39.167
- Well, uh,

21:39.210 --> 21:41.778
you get in these big boats,
and it takes us

21:41.822 --> 21:43.824
right up to where the water's
coming down.

21:43.867 --> 21:45.391
Right up to the edge.

21:45.434 --> 21:47.218
If we're lucky, we might
actually see some people

21:47.262 --> 21:49.395
coming over in barrels.

21:49.438 --> 21:51.701
- It's a thing
at Niagara Falls.

21:54.748 --> 22:01.798
♪

22:21.165 --> 22:24.430
- $7.50.
Would you like a bag with that?

22:24.473 --> 22:31.741
♪

22:35.092 --> 22:38.182
♪

22:40.097 --> 22:47.104
♪

23:07.864 --> 23:09.518
- You aren't real.

23:09.562 --> 23:11.172
You aren't!

23:13.174 --> 23:15.045
You aren't real!

23:15.089 --> 23:17.831
You're not--you're not real!
- Shh.

23:19.223 --> 23:20.311
- It's okay.

23:20.355 --> 23:22.052
It's okay.
Hey, it's okay.

23:22.096 --> 23:23.880
- Shh.

23:23.924 --> 23:26.274
♪

23:26.317 --> 23:28.319
I'm gonna take you home, okay?

23:28.363 --> 23:30.191
Okay.
It's okay.

23:30.234 --> 23:32.149
I'm gonna get you out of here.

23:32.193 --> 23:34.151
Who are you?

23:34.195 --> 23:35.544
♪

23:35.588 --> 23:37.807
- It's gonna be okay.

23:37.851 --> 23:44.901
♪

23:51.168 --> 23:53.301
♪

23:53.344 --> 23:55.042
Where are we going?

23:55.085 --> 23:56.870
Mosswood isn't this far.

23:56.913 --> 23:59.046
- Everything's gonna be
okay soon, I promise.

24:01.004 --> 24:02.223
♪

24:02.266 --> 24:03.964
Where are you taking me?
- I'm just here

24:04.007 --> 24:05.313
to help you out.
Don't worry.

24:05.356 --> 24:07.141
I'll explain everything
once we get

24:07.184 --> 24:09.317
a little bit further, okay?

24:09.360 --> 24:16.367
♪

24:24.114 --> 24:25.594
Who are you?
- I'll tell you

24:25.638 --> 24:27.117
as soon as we get
a little further out.

24:27.161 --> 24:28.902
- Tell me now!
Tell me who you are!

24:28.945 --> 24:30.338
Tell me who you are right now!
- Hey! Hey, stop it!

24:30.381 --> 24:32.122
- No!
- Hey, sit down!

24:32.166 --> 24:33.863
Hey, stop it!
- I'm gonna jump out!

24:33.907 --> 24:35.909
Tell me who you are!
- Julian, stop!

24:35.952 --> 24:37.388
Sit down!
- Tell me who you are!

24:37.432 --> 24:39.216
- Stop it! Stop!

24:39.260 --> 24:41.044
Stop it!
- No!

24:41.088 --> 24:42.350
♪

24:42.393 --> 24:43.612
Julian, stop it!

24:43.656 --> 24:45.832
- Stop it! Stop!

24:45.875 --> 24:47.050
Please!
Can you just look at me

24:47.094 --> 24:48.399
for one second?

24:48.443 --> 24:51.141
- I'm your mom!
I'm your mother!

24:51.185 --> 24:53.361
♪

24:53.404 --> 24:55.363
I'm sorry.
I'm your mom.

24:59.236 --> 25:01.935
I'm sorry.

25:01.978 --> 25:03.937
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

25:03.980 --> 25:06.635
I didn't want to tell you
like that, but I--

25:06.679 --> 25:08.245
we just don't have
very much time,

25:08.289 --> 25:10.030
and once we get a little bit
further out, I will--

25:10.073 --> 25:11.161
I will tell you everything,
okay?

25:11.205 --> 25:13.076
I promise.

25:13.120 --> 25:14.948
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

25:14.991 --> 25:17.124
- Hey, hey.

25:17.167 --> 25:19.430
I really don't want to do this,
but I just can't have you

25:19.474 --> 25:21.171
jumping out of the van, and we
really don't have much time.

25:21.215 --> 25:22.390
Once we get to somewhere else,
I'll--

25:24.348 --> 25:25.393
♪

25:25.436 --> 25:27.221
Julian!

25:27.264 --> 25:29.310
Julian!

25:29.353 --> 25:31.617
Stop!

25:31.660 --> 25:33.923
Please stop!

25:38.493 --> 25:39.929
- Julian!

25:41.801 --> 25:44.368
Julian!

25:46.849 --> 25:48.503
Hey.

25:48.547 --> 25:50.113
It's okay.

25:50.157 --> 25:51.637
I'm sorry.

25:51.680 --> 25:54.727
I'm sorry about
what happened back there.

26:02.648 --> 26:05.520
I know Vera never told you
about me...

26:06.477 --> 26:08.828
But I used to live
at Mosswood, too.

26:10.133 --> 26:12.440
It's where I gave birth
to you.

26:13.397 --> 26:15.574
I chose your name.

26:17.619 --> 26:19.490
You don't...

26:19.534 --> 26:20.883
remember me...

26:20.927 --> 26:22.885
do you?

26:28.674 --> 26:31.111
♪ Down in the...

26:31.154 --> 26:33.592
♪ Valley

26:34.549 --> 26:35.855
♪ The valley

26:35.898 --> 26:38.553
♪ So low

26:39.728 --> 26:43.427
♪ Hang your head over

26:44.733 --> 26:47.649
♪ Hear the wind blow

26:53.481 --> 26:55.614
- Bess sang that to me.

26:56.745 --> 26:59.487
- I used to sing that to you
all the time.

27:00.444 --> 27:02.621
She learned it from me.

27:05.667 --> 27:08.452
Can you just give me a chance?

27:09.192 --> 27:11.499
If, after a few days,
you want to go back,

27:11.542 --> 27:12.674
I'll bring you back.

27:12.718 --> 27:15.155
I promise.

27:15.198 --> 27:17.810
I just want to get to know you.

27:21.552 --> 27:23.946
You must be starving.

27:26.601 --> 27:28.603
I have this.

27:30.561 --> 27:32.476
It's okay.

27:38.787 --> 27:41.529
It's just a granola bar.

27:41.572 --> 27:42.922
So...

27:42.965 --> 27:49.972
♪

27:55.282 --> 27:56.675
♪

27:56.718 --> 27:58.764
Is it okay?

28:00.940 --> 28:02.550
♪

28:02.593 --> 28:04.726
- Found the vehicle.
All clear.

28:04.770 --> 28:11.777
♪

28:15.041 --> 28:16.564
- It's okay, honey.

28:16.607 --> 28:18.522
Let's go this way.

28:18.566 --> 28:20.220
Come on.

28:20.263 --> 28:23.527
♪

28:23.571 --> 28:25.660
- Any ideas where she'd be
taking him?

28:25.704 --> 28:27.009
- No clue.

28:28.750 --> 28:30.012
I mean, he's safe.

28:30.056 --> 28:31.971
- She just wants him back.

28:32.014 --> 28:34.669
I don't think
she would hurt him.

28:34.713 --> 28:36.845
- Yeah, but we don't know
for sure.

28:39.848 --> 28:42.590
I think we ought to add her
to the Amber Alert.

28:56.082 --> 28:57.997
What?

29:00.042 --> 29:02.784
- All she ever wanted
was a family.

29:05.308 --> 29:07.571
She was always at our house.

29:08.747 --> 29:10.749
Birthdays...

29:11.750 --> 29:13.708
Holidays...

29:14.665 --> 29:17.059
Any excuse to come over,
she was there.

29:19.714 --> 29:22.064
She never wanted to go home.

29:24.850 --> 29:27.809
- I'd say you did everything
you could.

29:29.898 --> 29:32.074
- No, I didn't.

29:33.684 --> 29:35.034
I ruined it for her.

29:36.905 --> 29:39.821
I did it back then, and now
I gotta do it again.

29:39.865 --> 29:46.872
♪

29:48.656 --> 29:50.658
Yeah, I have to update

29:50.701 --> 29:52.921
the Amber Alert
for Julian Walker.

29:52.965 --> 29:57.099
He's traveling with a female,
30 years old.

29:57.143 --> 29:59.928
- My mother says that
I'm not guilty...

29:59.972 --> 30:01.974
♪

30:02.017 --> 30:04.063
But I know that I am.

30:04.106 --> 30:07.806
♪

30:07.849 --> 30:09.808
I did it.

30:09.851 --> 30:11.766
♪

30:11.810 --> 30:13.681
I did it.

30:13.724 --> 30:15.335
♪

30:15.378 --> 30:17.772
- It's more complicated
than that.

30:17.816 --> 30:23.909
♪

30:25.911 --> 30:29.088
♪

30:31.003 --> 30:36.356
♪

30:37.923 --> 30:39.881
- Anthony, Misha,

30:39.925 --> 30:42.101
Grace, and J.B.

30:42.144 --> 30:44.930
I tried to stop them
but you weren't here.

30:44.973 --> 30:46.932
Everybody's getting fed up.

30:46.975 --> 30:48.629
- Of course they're getting
fed up.

30:48.672 --> 30:50.979
This is supposed to be
a sanctuary.

30:54.417 --> 30:56.898
- I want to find my son
and bring him home.

30:56.942 --> 30:58.639
- Even if you get him back,

30:58.682 --> 31:01.729
they're never gonna
let you keep him.

31:01.772 --> 31:03.949
You understand that, right?

31:06.995 --> 31:12.914
♪

31:12.958 --> 31:15.830
- This is all that Marin left
at The Grey Daughters.

31:15.874 --> 31:17.136
♪

31:17.179 --> 31:19.094
But...

31:19.138 --> 31:21.009
I found this.

31:21.053 --> 31:22.402
♪

31:22.445 --> 31:24.404
I know where she's going.

31:24.447 --> 31:29.713
♪

31:36.329 --> 31:38.461
- Let's go to the back.

31:40.072 --> 31:42.465
- Niagara Falls.

31:42.509 --> 31:44.990
- Yeah.

31:45.033 --> 31:46.252
Here, let's go here.

31:46.295 --> 31:52.432
♪

31:52.475 --> 31:55.217
- Laura,
this is Sister Joanne.

31:55.261 --> 31:58.003
The police were here
looking for you.

31:58.046 --> 32:01.223
One of them said she's
an old friend of yours.

32:01.267 --> 32:04.096
Apparently they have
an Amber Alert out for you

32:04.139 --> 32:06.228
and I'm very worried.

32:06.272 --> 32:08.274
Please call and let us know

32:08.317 --> 32:11.059
that you're okay.
Can you do that?

32:11.103 --> 32:18.153
♪

32:33.342 --> 32:35.475
- If you're really my mother...

32:36.432 --> 32:39.131
Why did you leave?

32:41.220 --> 32:44.310
- Because I felt like
I failed.

32:47.443 --> 32:49.619
- Being your mom.

32:51.099 --> 32:53.145
Being worthy.

32:58.541 --> 33:00.761
- A lot of places,

33:00.804 --> 33:03.285
most of them not so good.

33:05.113 --> 33:07.159
Got into drugs.

33:07.202 --> 33:10.379
Then I got sober...

33:10.423 --> 33:13.121
tried religion...

33:15.863 --> 33:19.214
But I could never get rid
of this pain.

33:24.350 --> 33:27.092
- Of missing you.

33:27.135 --> 33:29.442
I thought about you
all the time.

33:31.139 --> 33:33.228
How you were...

33:33.272 --> 33:35.317
who you were.

34:05.347 --> 34:07.132
- We should get gas.
- We still have

34:07.175 --> 34:09.221
1/4 of a tank.
- Let's just fill it up.

34:09.264 --> 34:11.223
Please.

34:11.266 --> 34:14.226
- Bess...

34:14.269 --> 34:16.445
Bess and Adam...

34:17.664 --> 34:19.579
They were--

34:20.623 --> 34:23.583
They--they were trying
to take me to you,

34:23.626 --> 34:26.107
weren't they?

34:33.332 --> 34:35.290
And I killed them.
- Hey.

34:35.334 --> 34:37.162
You didn't know.

34:42.167 --> 34:44.299
♪

34:46.214 --> 34:47.563
♪

34:47.607 --> 34:49.435
- Julian...

34:49.478 --> 34:51.524
- Julian, hey...

34:51.567 --> 34:53.265
- Get off me.

34:53.308 --> 34:54.875
♪

34:56.920 --> 34:59.314
- Hey, hey, hey.

34:59.358 --> 35:01.447
Julian, hey.

35:03.318 --> 35:04.624
- Hey, hey, hey!

35:04.667 --> 35:06.626
Julian!
Julian! Be quiet. Okay?

35:06.669 --> 35:08.323
- Julian!

35:08.367 --> 35:09.890
Come here, come here.

35:09.933 --> 35:11.457
- We're getting--

35:11.500 --> 35:13.676
we're getting off, okay?

35:19.639 --> 35:21.684
- Heather Novack.

35:23.512 --> 35:25.340
Hello?

35:30.345 --> 35:32.565
- It's me.

35:37.396 --> 35:42.227
♪

35:42.270 --> 35:43.924
- Hey.

35:43.967 --> 35:45.491
♪

35:45.534 --> 35:47.493
Are you okay?
- Yeah.

35:47.536 --> 35:49.582
Yeah, I'm okay.

35:49.625 --> 35:52.715
♪

35:52.759 --> 35:55.196
- Can't believe it's you.

35:55.240 --> 36:02.247
♪

36:03.291 --> 36:05.424
Is Julian okay?

36:05.467 --> 36:08.209
- He's good.

36:08.253 --> 36:09.950
Everything's okay.

36:09.993 --> 36:11.256
♪

36:11.299 --> 36:13.258
I know you're looking for me.

36:13.301 --> 36:16.957
♪

36:18.741 --> 36:20.395
♪

36:20.439 --> 36:22.702
- You have to leave us alone.

36:22.745 --> 36:24.312
♪

36:24.356 --> 36:26.662
- This is bigger
than just me, Marin.

36:26.706 --> 36:29.535
There's a lot of people looking
for you and Julian.

36:29.578 --> 36:31.754
- You could hold them off
for a day.

36:31.798 --> 36:33.974
- Marin, just come back.

36:34.017 --> 36:35.454
I'm on your side.

36:35.497 --> 36:37.717
I know Julian's your son.
I know...

36:37.760 --> 36:39.284
♪

36:39.327 --> 36:41.286
What you've been through.

36:41.329 --> 36:44.419
♪

36:44.463 --> 36:46.378
- No, you don't.

36:46.421 --> 36:47.422
♪

36:47.466 --> 36:49.990
- Then help me understand.

36:50.033 --> 36:52.645
Tell me where you are
and I'll come meet you.

36:52.688 --> 36:54.560
♪

36:54.603 --> 36:56.736
We can figure this out
together.

36:56.779 --> 36:58.564
♪

36:58.607 --> 37:00.696
Please.

37:00.740 --> 37:03.569
- You could throw them
off course,

37:03.612 --> 37:05.571
buy me some time.

37:05.614 --> 37:08.008
♪

37:08.051 --> 37:10.706
I've never had anything.

37:10.750 --> 37:12.795
This is the only thing I want.

37:12.839 --> 37:17.757
♪

37:17.800 --> 37:19.628
- I can't.

37:19.672 --> 37:23.589
♪

37:23.632 --> 37:25.417
- Fine.

37:25.460 --> 37:26.766
♪

37:26.809 --> 37:27.767
I have to go.

37:27.810 --> 37:29.682
- Wait, Marin...

37:31.771 --> 37:34.774
♪

37:36.645 --> 37:38.343
I'm sorry.

37:38.386 --> 37:42.303
♪

37:42.347 --> 37:44.566
- It's not your fault.

37:44.610 --> 37:45.698
♪

37:47.526 --> 37:54.576
♪

38:03.672 --> 38:06.719
♪

38:09.765 --> 38:12.507
- She called me on this phone.
I need a ping right away.

38:12.551 --> 38:13.552
These are exigent
circumstances,

38:13.595 --> 38:15.423
we've got a missing child.

38:17.120 --> 38:18.078
- Come on.

38:18.121 --> 38:20.080
Come on, we're here.

38:20.123 --> 38:27.348
♪

38:29.481 --> 38:30.873
- I'm hungry again.

38:30.917 --> 38:33.528
Is there something we can eat?
- I'm hungry, too.

38:33.572 --> 38:35.095
Can you just sit tight
for a second?

38:35.138 --> 38:37.663
I just have to make
a phone call.

38:54.897 --> 39:01.904
♪

39:12.828 --> 39:15.178
Hi.

39:15.222 --> 39:17.137
It's me.

39:17.180 --> 39:18.921
♪

39:18.965 --> 39:21.446
We're here.

39:21.489 --> 39:28.540
♪

39:32.761 --> 39:34.937
- Got it.

39:38.593 --> 39:40.726
She could be anywhere by now.

39:40.769 --> 39:42.597
- She's probably trying
for the border,

39:42.641 --> 39:45.600
but she's not gonna
make it across with Julian.

39:48.211 --> 39:49.691
Five Nations.

39:49.735 --> 39:51.867
- Right here.

39:51.911 --> 39:53.826
Take a look at this.

39:53.869 --> 39:55.654
Indian reservation straddles

39:55.697 --> 39:58.004
both sides of the border.

40:00.789 --> 40:04.619
I bet that's how she's planning
on getting across.

40:04.663 --> 40:09.668
♪

40:09.711 --> 40:12.192
- Yeah, all right.
Thanks, Brick.

40:12.235 --> 40:14.673
They ID'd our girl in the lake.

40:14.716 --> 40:16.805
Britt Jacobs.
She was a patient at Deacons,

40:16.849 --> 40:18.503
went missing several years ago.

40:18.546 --> 40:20.243
She had no connection
with Mosswood.

40:20.287 --> 40:22.594
Probably committed suicide.

40:22.637 --> 40:26.772
♪

40:26.815 --> 40:28.774
- Okay, here we are.

40:28.817 --> 40:30.950
Five Nations.

40:32.821 --> 40:35.607
♪

40:35.650 --> 40:38.784
Okay, looks like these guys
are onto something.

40:38.827 --> 40:40.786
What do you think?

40:40.829 --> 40:41.961
♪

40:42.004 --> 40:43.658
- Let's follow them.

40:46.705 --> 40:52.798
♪

40:55.844 --> 41:02.895
♪

41:12.034 --> 41:18.998
♪

41:21.609 --> 41:28.660
♪

41:32.315 --> 41:39.540
♪

41:51.596 --> 41:54.555
- ♪ Down in the valley

41:54.599 --> 41:57.732
♪ The valley so low

41:58.690 --> 42:01.867
♪ Hang your head over

42:01.910 --> 42:05.653
♪ Hear the wind blow

42:05.697 --> 42:10.615
♪ Roses love sunshine

42:10.658 --> 42:13.792
♪ Violets love dew

42:15.358 --> 42:18.753
♪ Angels in heaven

42:19.885 --> 42:22.627
♪ Know I love you

42:25.673 --> 42:26.935
♪
